            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "zrEBy1CwWlJElSv7",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Pallid Curse",
            "sort": 1300000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "free"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A sanctum guardian deals void damage on a creature within 30 feet)</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The void damage scars the target's soul, infecting it with Urgathoa's presence. The target must attempt a @Check[fortitude|dc:32] save with the following effects.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target suffers no additional effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1} and gains weakness to void 5 until the end of its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2} and gains weakness to void 5; this weakness has an unlimited duration. If the target dies while this curse remains in effect, the curse ends, but the target automatically rises as an undead creature (the GM picks one of the same level as the target) that goes on to serve Urgathoa in its unlife. If the target is destroyed in its new undead form, it reverts to its original living form but is dying 3.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but weakness to void 10.</p>"
                },
                "frequency": {
                    "max": 1,
                    "per": "day"
                },
                "publication": {
